    <div class="TextContent"><strong>New rules for bringing cameras and equipment on the floor</strong><br />
<br />
Following recent global tragedies, CES is implementing enhanced security measures surrounding the upcoming CES&reg; 2016 to produce a safer event. While there are no known, credible threats against CES, we are augmenting our standard security procedures as a precautionary measure.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Media attending CES will be subject to the same security and safety restrictions and procedures as general show attendees with some allowances. Please reference our<a href="https://www.cesweb.org/Register-Plan/New-CES-Security-Procedures.aspx" target="_blank"> main security page</a> for general security guidelines.<br />
<br />
To view the complete list of security policies and procedures for CES 2016 visit <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/security" target="_blank">www.CESweb.org/security</a>.</div>
